<!--  Define which variables in the template can be passed in when the
      template is run via the z/OSMF REST API. Any variable that is
      passed on the REST API replaces the value of the variable
      defined in the template.

      Therefore, it makes sense to restrict some variables to the
      template, which is what gets approved. However, to enable
      different UKO instances to be provisioned with different
      configurations, based on the same z/OSMF template, it
      is necessary to allow a subset of the variables to
      be set.

      The file can be modified to suit the needs of your business. -->

<atCreate name="UKO_SERVER_STC_USER" scope="instance" prompt="true" required="false"/>
